      <bioghist id="aspace_cb5d583f298cb7fbbe51a922e4fb847e">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Francis John Baker was born August 10, 1869, in Somerset, England. A corn merchant by trade, he joined the 48th North Somerset Imperial Yeomanry, arriving in South Africa in 1901. Lance Corporal Baker was honorably discharged in 1902.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_17e8d5e42e118c03afe6ecadcc4e2bc2">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The collection comprises a manuscript diary covering the years 1901-1902, written in 1912 from notes taken during that time period. Baker provides lengthy, detailed descriptions of his experiences in the Boer War and daily camp life. Military documents, family correspondence, and photographs are included.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
